projects

Project 4: Reconstitution of endocytic actin network

recent progress

  • first evidence that correlation using beads is feasible!
  • summary of working CLEM sample prep:
    1. dope in fiducial 0.5 µm beads after fixing reaction with 2 µm beads
    2. deposit on gridded MatTek dish and immobilize in agarose
    3. identify regions with unique 3D arrangement of beads and positive fluorescence
    4. capture GFP, lipid, and bright field z-stacks at 4x, 20x, and 60x
    5. infiltrate and polymerize resin in sample
    6. check stability of sample after resin polymerization by light microscopy
    7. cut out sub-grid regions from resin
    8. serial sections every ~100 nm (~70 nm thickness)
    9. visually correlate sections back to fluorescence data
    10. collect correlated TEM data!

next steps

weeks of <2021-10-11 Mon> to <2021-10-22 Fri>
  • prepare real experimental samples in technical replicates
  • collect correlative data
week of <2021-10-25 Mon>
  • determine whether there is a difference in membrane shape between high and low fluorescence beads
    • come up with some metric of scoring if so
weeks of <2021-10-25 Mon> to <2021-11-12 Fri>
  • if there are differences, collect triplicate data and do statistical test
